    <p style="color:#42474e; font-size:1.125rem; max-width:620px; margin:1.5rem auto 2.5rem; line-height:1.8;">
      Generic AI tools don't know your policies, your products, or your processes. We build AI tools trained on your company's own data, so your team gets accurate, context-aware answers instantly.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:16px; justify-content:center; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <button onclick="openModal(this)" data-source="internal_hero" class="btn-primary">Book a Free Discovery Call</button>
      <a href="#what-we-build" class="btn-outline">See What We Build ↓</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

<!-- HERO IMAGE -->
<div style="position:relative; overflow:hidden; height:260px;">
  <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1460925895917-afdab827c52f?w=1400&q=80&auto=format&fit=crop" alt="Internal AI tools and business intelligence dashboards" loading="eager" fetchpriority="high" width="1400" height="260" style="width:100%; height:100%; object-fit:cover; object-position:center 40%;" />
  <div style="position:absolute; inset:0; background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(0,104,117,0.20),rgba(0,37,59,0.40));"></div>
</div>

<!-- WHAT ARE INTERNAL AI TOOLS -->
<section class="section" aria-labelledby="explain-heading">
  <div class="container">
    <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
      <h2 id="explain-heading" style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">What Are Internal AI Tools?</h2>
      <p style="color:#42474e; font-size:1.0625rem; line-height:1.85; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
        Internal AI tools are AI-powered systems deployed inside your organization, trained on your company's own data, and accessible only to your team. Unlike consumer AI tools that answer from generic internet knowledge, internal AI tools know exactly what your company does, how it operates, what its policies are, and what information is relevant to each employee's role.
      </p>
      <p style="color:#42474e; font-size:1.0625rem; line-height:1.85; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
        The most common form is a company knowledge base AI: an assistant that can answer any question about your products, processes, policies, or history by reading your internal documents and synthesizing a precise answer. Instead of searching through a SharePoint folder for 15 minutes or pinging a senior colleague for the fifth time this week, an employee types their question and gets the right answer in seconds, with a citation to the source document.
      </p>
      <p style="color:#42474e; font-size:1.0625rem; line-height:1.85;">
        Beyond knowledge retrieval, internal AI tools can handle operational work: drafting documents in your company's voice, analyzing internal data and surfacing insights, managing onboarding workflows, or acting as a 24/7 internal help desk for HR and IT questions. The scope is defined by what your team actually needs, and every tool is deployed in your environment with your access controls, so data stays exactly where it belongs.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- PROBLEM CARDS -->
<section class="section" aria-labelledby="problem-heading">
  <div class="container">
    <div style="text-align:center; margin-bottom:3rem;">
      <h2 id="problem-heading">The Problem With Generic AI Tools</h2>
